The paper discusses privacy in constraint satisfaction problems, which is a topic that falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes the use of distributed computation to solve these problems, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also presents algorithms and experiments, which fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
